RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 73. Maiden Claiming Purse 18000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $17,500. In the event that this race is taken off the turf it will be contested at One Mile and Seventy Yards on the main track. (Rail at 10 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ARMAVIR settled off the pace in a good position, rallied between horses on the second turn, closed steadily, wore down the PAINTSVILLE to get up late and held off the late charge of DAPPER DUDE. DAPPER DUDE was allowed to settle and raced in the back, rallied into the turn, swung wide entering the stretch, found his best stride late and was gaining late. PAINTSVILLE vied inside to the second turn, drew off for a clear lead, led to late stretch and was outclosed. ELECTRIC CHARGE was unhurried early and trailed the field, angled out at the top of the stretch, finished well and was gaining late. ICE VORTEX raced mid pack, rallied into the second turn, bid six wide to get within range and hung late. HANDSOFFTHEGOODS was fractious loading and failed to threaten in an even effort. DARK SOLUTION stumbled at the start, vied three across to the second turn, tired and stopped. INDIO GUAPO vied between horses to the second turn, tired and stopped.
